texts.text: Those who stray from the path of righteousness will ultimately suffer.
Show me that you have the power to overcome that, Liberators.
Go!
>The angels attack on Shaddai's command!
Prepare yourselves!
Devil Download!
*Roar*
>Your demons parry the angels' attacks!
>But become completely surrounded moments later.
Liberators, you must summon more demons.
We shall defeat them all.
This is gonna be rough...
And you're just here to watch us suffer, Shaddai?
Yeah, what the hell!
You helped us out that other time!
Why are you doing this to us now?
Why are we being tested like this?!
Be victorious, keep advancing and Sabaoth will surely tell you.
But for now, you must fight.
Grr.... Dammit...!

Not gonna talk, huh?
Fine, we'll play your game.
Aight, y'all, let's do this!
>The battle ensues!

*Pant*
We've defeated so many!
Yeah.
But Shaddai might be waiting for us at the end of all this.
So battle our way through these mobs and fight the boss after that?
I hope not...
Chatting? At a time like this? You seem awfully confident in yourselves.
But no longer!

*Wince*
You're not winning that easily!
Yo, got that right!
*Roar*
This is it!
Eat this!
*Groan*
>The last angel falls...
We did it!
Aight, now what...?
>You all turn around while getting into position...
>And see Shaddai now moving towards you...
Well done, Liberators.
I deem you worthy and you will now proceed to your next trial.
Huh?
Yo, just like that?
You were given a trial and achieved victory.
But if you truly wish to save this world, you will need to act "righteously" during your next trial.
Now, excuse me...
>Shaddai begins to disappear.

Yo, Shaddai, hold up!
What do mean by actin' "righteously"?
It is not my place to say.
I simply hope that you do not let me down.
Let you down...?
Oh, wait! One more thing!

About Elisa...
Is she in heaven now?
Sorry, I really need to know.
Elisa...? The young girl you became friends with?
God's true children will all be saved.
The word of God is eternal.
Now, Liberators, hurry and go forth.
>Shaddai vanishes...
It's gone.
I know I'm not the smartest person out there.
But Shaddai meant "yes" by that, right?
Yes, I believe so.
Don't worry, I'm sure Elisa's in a better place now.

Okay, good!
I feel a lot better now.
Yo, we're still in the dark about whatever's goin' on here.
Shaddai did say that this is just our "first trial".
At the very least, we've cleared this hurdle.
But to be honest, this was easier than what I expected...
I feel the same way.
I won't deny that the angels were strong and we struggled there for a bit...
But Shaddai did nothing as we pushed back against them.
He just "observed"...
So Shaddai isn't the one passing judgment or whatever here?
Yo, Vince, what do you mean?
Sabaoth said that Elohim and Shaddai brought it here, right?
But Elohim doesn't exactly like roundabout schemes.
If it doesnâ€™t like this world, it's just gonna erase everything.
I really doubt it'll care if a couple more worlds get destroyed.
I see!
That may also explain why some of us aren't feeling so great.
So Shaddai and Elohim are keepin' Elohim on a short leash?
Yo, is that what's goin' on?
Hold on, that means Shaddai's a good guy, right?
Hah! You're way too soft, kid.

"Act 'righteously' during your next trial."
"Do not let me down."
Don't you know what that means?
It's a threat. If we don't do what they want us to do, that's it.
Wait, what?!
But we still don't really know what's goin' on, so we just gotta keep goin'.
So back to the stairs, y'all.
Yo, get ready for some more cardio.
Please, no more...!
Quit complaining. You used to be a soldier, right?
You should be begging me to be carried by you, pig.

*Gasp*
You're right!
So...
No.
Okay...
>The Liberators start making their way back...
What's up, Honey?
(It feels like someone's watching us...)
No, it's probably nothing...
Still, I just don't understand what these Godly spirits are trying to do.
Got that right.
But there's more to it than just them.
Humans probably aren't ever meant to know what God's trying to say.
To be fair, I couldn't care less...
